<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,361,387]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Foreleg reddish; tibia ventrally with yellow setae, posterodorsally all the with black macrosetae and yellow setae. Hind femur with thin, long, pale setae, and some scattered thick, long, black setae. Hind tibia dorsobasally with dense, white setae, remainder of dorsal surface with dense, brown setae combined with a few yellow ones, and scattered black macrosetae; ventrally on basal third with short, brown setae, on apical two thirds with long white thick setae. Hind tarsus ventrally with long white setae and a few black macrosetae. Abdominal tergite I without setae, II to X with yellow setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" box="[199,1073,577,605]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,577,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[427,532,578,605]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total body length 
<quantity box="[754,836,578,604]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity box="[987,1069,578,605]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,614,640]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Head</emphasis>
: light-brown. Scape light-brown basally darkening apically; remaining antennal segments missing. Ocellar triangle yellow. Gena with yellow setae; facial gibbosity developed on ventral half, face with a non pubescent rounded area between the antennae and the proboscis exposing brown cuticle, face with yellow macrosetae mixed with black macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[420,508,722,748]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) wing. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Visible maxillary palpus yellow. Proboscis black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1096,1185,722,748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Thorax</emphasis>
: reddish-brown. Postpronotum in dorsal view with yellow and black setae, macrosetae at margins with apex darker than base; mesonotum laterally with four brown areas, and one large medial elongate brown area, with black short setae and black macrosetae, both on the lateral margin; scutellum with long orange setae and some black macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1421,830,856]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) wing. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); katatergite with long orange setae, tegula with black macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[896,984,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) wing. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Foreleg reddish; coxa with long, light yellow setas; femur with black setae and some black macrosetae on entire surface; tibia with black setae dorsally mixed with black and yellow setae apically, ventrally with a row of yellow setae; tarsi with dense thick black setae. Midleg reddish, both femur and tibia with black macrosetae mixed with black macrosetae. Hind leg reddish; tibia longer than femur, coxa with long, light yellow setae; femur ventrally with yellow and black setae, dorsally with some short yellow setae sparsely distributed; tibia with short yellow setae dorsobasally, remainder of dorsal surface with dense, brown setae combined with a few white ones, and scattered black macrosetae, setae increasing in size towards apex; ventrally with brown setae on basal third, apical two thirds with white setae. First tarsal segment only with black setae anteriorly, second to fifth tarsomeres with white setae and setae. Wing coloration opaque brown; C vein with short black setae, presence of setae beyond humeral crossvein (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1092,1189,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) wing. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1106,1223,1189,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Abdomen</emphasis>
: black. T1 without dorsal setae, T2–8 yellow setose dorsally and ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[785,868,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) wing. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig 1A</figureCitation>
); ventrally with yellow setae, homogeneously distributed (
<figureCitation box="[254,340,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[200,1386,179,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) wing. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529449" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529449/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Epandria short and black, with yellow setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" box="[199,411,1297,1323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1297,1323]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1333,1359]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species takes the name “gauteovan” after the Tayrona goddess as a tribute to the place from which the 
<typeStatus box="[332,430,1368,1394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected. In the Tayrona culture this goddess is considered the mother of all things. The name is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1439,1465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Distribution.</emphasis>
This new species is only known so far from the Tayrona National Park in the Caribbean region in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,290,1475,1501]" name="Colombia" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Colombia</collectingCountry>
at sea level (
<figureCitation box="[437,499,1475,1501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1123]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map of northern South America with distribution of Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. and Mallophora kalos sp. nov. in Colombia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529459/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1511,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[323,582,1511,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,582,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Mallophora gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[589,680,1511,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[589,680,1511,1537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[1016,1150,1511,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1150,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Mallophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the brown body color and the color pattern of the ventral setae of the hind tibia, in which there are brown setae on the basal third, whereas the apical two thirds have white setae; dorsally the setae are brown, except for a small area of white setae, increasing in size towards apex. Following the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." box="[689,978,1618,1644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, this species might be confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Artigas &amp; Angulo, 1980" authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." box="[275,545,1654,1680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of the setae on the hind tibia increase in length toward the apical third, and by the white setae on the hind femur. Nonetheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[757,910,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[757,910,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black body, hyaline wings and epandrium with white setae, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[450,606,1726,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[450,606,1726,1751]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[613,704,1726,1752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[613,704,1726,1752]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a reddish-brown body, the wings are opaque brown, and the epandria has yellow setae, same as the abdomen. More importantly, it seems from the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[1275,1430,1761,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[1275,1430,1761,1787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that the color pattern of the hind tibia is different, because in this species the basal has white setae, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">M. gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,364,1833,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[275,364,1833,1859]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
only the apical two thirds ventrally are white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,253,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
Although the description is based on a single specimen, we argue that it represents a new species based on the particular color pattern of the setae on the hind legs, especially on the hind tibia. Previous evidence (
<bibRefCitation author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo, 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kohler, A. &amp; Klein, J. &amp; Assmann, J." box="[320,534,1940,1966]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="432 - 438" refId="ref5774" refString="Kohler, A., Klein, J. &amp; Assmann, J. (2013) Novas ocorrencias de Mallophora Macquart, 1834 (Diptera, Asilidae) no Rio Grande Do Sul: chave de identificac &quot; o e distribuic &quot; o. Brazilian Journal of Biosciences, 11 (4), 432 - 438. [http: // www. ufrgs. br / seerbio / ojs / index. php / rbb / article / view / 27]" type="journal article" year="2013">
Kohler 
<emphasis box="[405,469,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">et al.,</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and careful examination of additional species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[1097,1231,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1231,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Mallophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. Yepes unpubl. obs.), enable us to confirm that males of every species have a particular color pattern and chaetotaxy on the hind legs. Therefore, having a single male allows us to hypothesize that this specimen belongs to a new species.
</paragraph>
